President Donald Trump has proclaimed June 2020 as National Homeownership Month in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of homeownership for Americans and acknowledges the role it plays in their health, independence, and well-being. The President emphasizes his administration's efforts to protect homeowners affected by the coronavirus outbreak, including the signing of the CARES Act, which provided financial assistance and mortgage-payment relief. The administration also aims to reform the housing finance system and support affordable homeownership by eliminating unnecessary regulations and investing in underserved communities. The proclamation expresses optimism that the economy will rebound, creating jobs and opportunities for Americans to achieve the American dream of owning a home.